After video of a man attempting to abduct a barista through a drive-thru window early Monday went viral, police in Washington state announced they had arrested a suspect. Security camera footage released by Auburn Police Department showed the man, from the driver’s seat of a Chevrolet Silverado pickup truck, trying to loop a zip tie on the female employee’s arm as she passed him change. The barista, who was working alone, broke free and the man drove off. Watch the video here: “After overwhelming support from the community, APD has arrested a suspect in this case,” police announced on Tuesday. The footage has garnered more than 2 million views on Twitter. The suspect, whose identity has not been revealed, faces attempted kidnapping and other charges, KIRO-TV reported.